binge playing it. Also BIG PLUS no micro transactions and no forced waiting 
to pad it out.

The gameplay is that classic RPG with the timing mechanic so it keeps you active . This rewards you with extra hits on an enemy or taking less damage from attacks. The art style is not the same from the show but instead takes on a simpler version of the look, yet it still feels like another episode of Steven universe. The game only has 2 modes that being normal and the other being diamond which beefs up the enimies and the damage they deal, just your typical hard mode. The game does take place during Steven's early stages so he is more of a support character more than active fighter.

Usually you'd be right to avoid cashcow series turning into terrible games and spin-offs, but this title is legitimately worth your time.  It is basically South Park: Stick of Truth, but with a Steven Universe plot, visuals, references, and even new stuff you'd expect to find within the show itself. Not only that, but it's fresh. It doesn't feel like rehashed material, but like an episode of its own. The characters have character, they're written as you would expect them to speak, and there is partial voicing of the dialogue in the most important places.  I have only played through the first world and a little into the second so far, and there has already been a decent amount of referencing to the show that could be considered spoilers. I'm not too sure where this game would be set timeline-wise, but it's definitely somewhat deep into season 1.   Give it a chance. I don't think you'll be disappointed if you love Steven Universe.

Raised my standard for mobile games. Great gameplay that allows for either a casual or more strategic approach. Beautiful visuals, it just looks all around great (designs, background, etc). Great character interactions and the voices are great as you'd expect. At first I just got excited by watching and touching the gems (the screen!) and getting their reactions, like if I had my own mini-gems to interact with at the palm of my hand, hah.  What else, it has nice music and sounds, too, some nice secrets, maybe a couple of annoyances (right now I can only think about a type of enemy that can get irritating). I wish it was longer and more expansive (a bigger PC/console sequel would be awesome, for instance), but it's definitely worth it and all around a very good game that surprised me.  Oh, and of course, a must-play for fans of the show!
